</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C294D79803CFF95FEC42F4EFD4BFED0" authority="Silvestri, 1946" authorityName="Silvestri" authorityYear="1946" box="[338,754,346,371]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oecidiophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimellus">
<emphasis id="B95DEAE8803CFF95FEC42F4EFDF5FED0" box="[338,588,346,371]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Oecidiophilus mimellus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB84B0B803CFF95FDC32F4EFD4BFED0" author="Silvestri, F." box="[597,754,346,371]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="299 - 334" refId="ref7364" refString="Silvestri, F. 1946. Descrizioni e notizie di Staphylinidae termitofili sudamericani. Commentationes Pontificia Academia Scientiarum, 10: 299 - 334." type="journal article" year="1946">Silvestri, 1946</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by monotypy (not 
<emphasis id="B95DEAE8803CFF95FECF2F6EFE60FE30" box="[345,473,378,403]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<taxonomicName id="4C294D79803CFF95FECF2F6EFE6CFE30" box="[345,469,378,403]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oecidiophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oglobinii">O. oglobinii</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
nomen nudum, as originally designated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB84B0B803CFF95FEDB2F8EFE53FE10" author="Silvestri, F." box="[333,490,410,435]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="299 - 334" refId="ref7364" refString="Silvestri, F. 1946. Descrizioni e notizie di Staphylinidae termitofili sudamericani. Commentationes Pontificia Academia Scientiarum, 10: 299 - 334." type="journal article" year="1946">Silvestri, 1946</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3336571803CFF95FF3C2FCEFB3DFE50" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9636FA803CFF95FF3C2FCEFE97FC90" blockId="10.[170,795,474,819]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B95DEAE8803CFF95FF3C2FCEFE22FE50" bold="true" box="[170,411,474,499]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Redescription: Head</emphasis>
elongate, about 1.4 times as long as wide, not widest behind the eyes; 
<emphasis id="B95DEAE8803CFF95FDCD2FEEFD29FDB0" bold="true" box="[603,656,506,531]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">gula</emphasis>
narrow, lateral margins almost parallel; 
<emphasis id="B95DEAE8803CFF95FE642C0EFD73FD90" bold="true" box="[498,714,538,563]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">foramen magnum</emphasis>
broad, about one third the head width; mandibles symmetrical; maxillary palpi with 4 palpomeres, fourth palpomere almost the length of the third; 
<emphasis id="B95DEAE8803CFF95FE722C6EFDC8FD30" bold="true" box="[484,625,634,659]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">prementum</emphasis>
with palpi with 3 palpomeres, and ligula slightly incised in the middle; 
<emphasis id="B95DEAE8803CFF95FF3C2CAEFEA2FD70" bold="true" box="[170,283,698,723]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">antennae</emphasis>
with 11 antennomeres, scape as long as antennomeres II and III combined, III‑X slightly longer than wide, progressively and slightly decreasing in length towards apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9636FA803CFF95FCF32ECEFAA8FEB0" blockId="10.[869,1493,218,275]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B95DEAE8803CFF95FCF32ECEFC06FF50" bold="true" box="[869,959,218,243]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Thorax:</emphasis>
Wings present and broken; first metatarsomere as long as second and third combined.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9636FA803CFF95FCF32F2EFB3DFE50" blockId="10.[869,1493,314,499]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B95DEAE8803CFF95FCF32F2EFC63FEF0" bold="true" box="[869,986,314,339]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Abdomen</emphasis>
highly physogastric and scarcely setose, covered mostly by short and medium bristles; tergite IX without macrosetae; tergite X suboval, with midsized bristles at apex. 
<emphasis id="B95DEAE8803CFF95FBB02F8EFB25FE10" bold="true" box="[1062,1180,410,435]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Aedeagus</emphasis>
with phallobase large and bulbous, apex of median lobe with membranous structure with sinuous pattern.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3336571803CFF94FCF32C0EFE9FFE90" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="12" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9636FA803CFF94FCF32C0EFE9FFE90" blockId="10.[869,1494,538,819]" lastBlockId="11.[94,718,218,307]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="12" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B95DEAE8803CFF95FCF32C0EFC6AFD90" bold="true" box="[869,979,538,563]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Remarks:</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D79803CFF95FBC82C0EFB49FD90" authorityName="Silvestri" authorityYear="1946" box="[1118,1264,538,563]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oecidiophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95DEAE8803CFF95FBC82C0EFB49FD90" box="[1118,1264,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Oecidiophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
until now was represented by a single enigmatic species from 
<collectingCountry id="F33E766A803CFF95FAF72C2EFA6BFDF0" box="[1377,1490,570,595]" name="Argentina" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, Loreto (
<collectingRegion id="49EDF818803CFF95FC282C4EFB9FFDD0" box="[958,1062,602,627]" country="Argentina" name="Misiones" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Misiones</collectingRegion>
), known only from the 
<typeStatus id="54928858803CFF95FAAD2C4EFA19FDD0" box="[1339,1440,602,627]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">holotype</typeStatus>
and the original description (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB84B0B803CFF95FBE12C6EFAAEFD30" author="Silvestri, F." box="[1143,1303,634,659]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="299 - 334" refId="ref7364" refString="Silvestri, F. 1946. Descrizioni e notizie di Staphylinidae termitofili sudamericani. Commentationes Pontificia Academia Scientiarum, 10: 299 - 334." type="journal article" year="1946">Silvestri, 1946</bibRefCitation>
). Herein, the second species of the genus is described, representing the first record of 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D79803CFF95FB9E2CAEFB23FD70" authorityName="Silvestri" authorityYear="1946" box="[1032,1178,698,723]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oecidiophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95DEAE8803CFF95FB9E2CAEFB23FD70" box="[1032,1178,698,723]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Oecidiophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for 
<collectingCountry id="F33E766A803CFF95FB5D2CAEFAB0FD70" box="[1227,1289,698,723]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. The wings of the analyzed specimen were broken in a similar way to that found in 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D79803CFF95FC512CEEFBF6FCB0" authorityName="Silvestri" authorityYear="1946" box="[967,1103,762,787]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Fonsechellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95DEAE8803CFF95FC512CEEFBF6FCB0" box="[967,1103,762,787]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fonsechellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species.It is presumed that individuals lose their wings in the same way as 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D79803CFF95FA8B2D0EFA1CFC90" authorityName="Silvestri" authorityYear="1946" box="[1309,1445,794,819]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Fonsechellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95DEAE8803CFF95FA8B2D0EFA1CFC90" box="[1309,1445,794,819]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fonsechellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and it would not be impressive if this phenomenon was even more embracing across other related genera in the subtribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D79803DFF94FF012F0EFE9BFE90" box="[151,290,282,307]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Termoiceina">Termoiceina</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
